Provides: mangowc, wayland-compositor
Conflicts: mangowc
Replaces: mangowc
Description: Lightweight and fast Wayland compositor based on dwl
 Mango is a Wayland compositor that builds upon the lightweight and fast
 philosophy of dwl. It provides smooth animations, excellent xwayland support,
 flexible window layouts, and rich window states without compromising on
 functionality or performance.
 .
 Features include tag-based workspaces, sway-like scratchpads, IPC support,
 and window effects like blur and shadows via scenefx.

Package: mangowc
Architecture: all
Section: oldlibs
Priority: optional
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, mangowm
Description: Transitional package for mangowm
 This is a transitional package to ease the upgrade from mangowc to mangowm.
 It can be safely removed.
